<section id="Rules">
    <h2>Rules</h2>
    <p>Bowling, Batting, Fielding rules:
Matches will played with Vicky / Similar Brand Light Tennis ball.
Each Inning will be of 6 Overs for all categories.
Each player must bowl 1 over, Only 1 bowler/Inning can bowl 2 Overs.
Incase of team playing with Less than 5 Players, Batting Team’s captain will decide whose over to
be repeated from bowling team for completing 6 Overs.
Once Batsman scores Individual 35 Runs, has to get declared & Next Batsman to play onwards, declared batsman can bat again in same inning once team is all out.
Bowling action/technique: Stand with both feet parallel inside the marked box and release the ball above shoulders (Throw), Underarm action not allowed, however for few Categories basis on both team’s captains mutual agreement, minor deviation in action can be agreed. Lifting legs while bowling is not allowed & will be treated as ‘No Ball’. Video will be shared on the What’s App group & demo will also be given on 7th Jan.
In case of a Match Tie, a Super Over of 1 over will be played. Only 3 batsmen are allowed to bat. The last player for batting is permitted.
LBW, Leg Byes, Byes, and Runners are not allowed throughout the tournament.
Wide, No Ball runs will be counted.
Runs on Overthrow is allowed.
Running between Wicket is mandatory.
Last Man Lucky (Will get batting)

GENERAL RULES.
The ground size will be the same for all categories.
Bowling pitch size will vary for each category.
Teams, Players must bring their own bats, Organizers will only arrange Balls & Stumps.
Plastic or synthetic Bats not allowed.
Only Players & Umpires will be allowed in Court at the time of Match.
Safety of Individual is most important.
Players to consider safety 1st while Playing, responsibility of Safety remains with Player.
Maximum Cooperation needed from Society Members to Organizers to make Event Successful &
strong appeal to all for maximum participation in all categories.
Final authority of any fine tuning in rules (need base) will be with Organizing Committee.
By participating in this tournament, all players acknowledge and accept that sports activities involve inherent risks of injury. The organizers shall not be held liable for any injuries, damages, or losses sustained by participants during the event</p>
